{"article_id":"AnWXZ1N1DPX6dAeT","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"When the novel coronavirus began spreading rapidly throughout the U.S. in late March ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"42 states and Washington , D.C. , issued stay-at-home orders","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that shuttered all or most nonessential businesses for an average of nearly 50 days ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"with some orders lasting as long as 70 days","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"( and counting ) .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"Over the same period , the U.S. has seen unprecedented job losses ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"with Thursday ' s report of 2.1 million initial claims now part of a tally of 41 million Americans","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who have filed for unemployment insurance since the second week of March .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Although last week ' s jobless claims declined at a faster rate","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"( -13.2 percent )","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"than they did the week before","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"( -9.0 percent ) ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the numbers involved remain immense by any historical standard :","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"There are a few shreds of encouraging news in the most recently compiled jobs data , though .","depth":4},{"id":14,"text":"For weeks , we ' ve been waiting for the sheer number of people on temporary layoff or furlough","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"- as opposed to permanent unemployment -","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"to return to work","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"and no longer show up in the official unemployment data .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"as the economy begins to open up in 36 of those 42 states with shutdown orders ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"one place","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"they might finally be appearing","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"is in the number of continued unemployment claims .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"As opposed to initial claims ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"which represent the number of newly unemployed people","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"filing for insurance ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"continued claims represent the total number of people","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"- newly unemployed or not -","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"whose claims were paid out in a given week .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"These claims run a week behind initial claims","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"because we don ' t know","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"how many of those will eventually be insured .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Now that we are months deep into the unemployment crisis ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"continued claims are arguably a better measure of the current state of joblessness in the U.S. than initial claims are -","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"and for the week","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"ending on May 16 ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"total continued claims declined for the first time since the last week of February ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"before economic disaster hit American shores .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"On top of laid-off workers","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"potentially going back to work ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"this decline also speaks to companies ' beginning to hire slightly more","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"than they have for most of the crisis .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Total job postings on the employment-search website Indeed have increased in each of the past three weeks .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"Before we get too optimistic , though ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"those numbers are still sharply worse than in the same time frame in 2019 :","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"The volume on May 1 was 39.3 percent worse than on the same date a year ago ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"but it was just 35.1 percent worse than 2019 on May 22 .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"Still , this is another data point","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"showing","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"that the unemployment situation has started to ever so slightly improve over the past few weeks .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Does that owe to states ' efforts","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"to reopen ?","depth":4},{"id":52,"text":"To look at this relationship ,","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"I asked Indeed for its job-posting trend data","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"broken out by state","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"and classified each applicable state","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"according to how long ago it ended statewide stay-at-home orders .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"The four states","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"that reopened the earliest","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"have been a mixed bag","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"since lifting stay-at-home orders .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"The job-posting trend in Alaska has increased by 8.8 percentage points over the past four weeks , relative to its final week with orders in place ;","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"similarly , Montana ' s trend is up by 4.9 points .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"But in the two more populous states , Colorado ' s job postings are down 0.8 points ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"and Mississippi ' s are down 5.7 points -","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"meaning that job postings are down more now","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"( relative to 2019 )","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"than they were","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"when statewide orders were in place .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"That ' s just a sample of four states , of course -","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"two of them ranking among the least populated in the country .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"But the group of states","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"that reopened three weeks ago","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"is larger","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"( 11 states )","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and has seen a similar pattern relative to states","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that waited longer","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"to reopen :","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"There could be some selection bias here :","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"States","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"that waited longer","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"may have been in a stronger economic position than those","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"desperate to reopen sooner","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"( although everything above is measured relative to each state ' s own jobs trend for its last week in lockdown ) .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"And states","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"that never issued stay-at-home orders","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"are , on average , down less in job postings from 2019","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"( -34.5 percent , as of May 22 )","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"than states","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"that still had orders in place as of May 22","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"( -38.3 percent ) .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"But those numbers are also indicative of how little power government orders may have to restart the job market anyway","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"when compared with the power of the virus itself .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"Polls show","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"that more than two-thirds of Americans remain somewhat or very concerned","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"that either they or someone","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"they know","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"will become infected with the coronavirus .","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"That has reshaped people ' s willingness","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"to go to restaurants and otherwise spend discretionary income , even in states","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"that have loosened restrictions on those activities .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"As economists have been saying for a while ,","depth":5},{"id":102,"text":"the only thing","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"that can fully inject life back into the economy","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"is getting the virus under control ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"which is more true now","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"- according to new daily cases -","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"than it was a month ago ,","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"regardless of whether stay-at-home orders were loosened .","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"And even with the total unemployment situation improving slightly this week ,","depth":5},{"id":110,"text":"more trouble is on the horizon .","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"The first wave of companies","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that were granted loans under the Payroll Protection Program","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"will have their expenses covered only through June 30 ,","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"after which we could see more potential job losses","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"- or temporary layoffs turned permanent .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"( The U.S. House passed a bill","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"to extend the window","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"to use PPP funds","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"by four months","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"and push back the deadline","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"to rehire workers through December ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"though it will face opposition in the Senate . )","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"And , of course , any economic progress could be derailed by the ever-present threat of another surge in cases .","depth":5},{"id":124,"text":"It ' s another reminder","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"that the virus is what ultimately started this financial crisis","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"-","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"and it will largely dictate the terms of the economic recovery .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":255,"left":220,"right":254,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":220,"left":177,"right":219,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":141,"right":176,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":140,"right":13,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":135,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":132,"righ